        <definition xml:id="definition TI8infinityint">
            <p>
                For a function <m>f(x)</m> and a constant <m>c</m>, we let <m>\displaystyle \int_c^\infty f(x) dx</m> denote <me>\int_c^\infty f(x) dx=\lim_{a\to\infty}\left( \int_c^a f(x) dx\right).</me>  So just as in limits, this value can be a real number, <m>\pm \infty</m> or undefined.
            </p>
            <p>
                Similarly <me>\int_{-\infty}^c f(x) dx=\lim_{a\to-\infty}\left( \int_a^c f(x) dx\right).</me>
            </p>
        </definition>
        
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Fabound">
            <p>
               Which of the following is <m>\displaystyle \int_1^a \frac{1}{x^2} dx</m> ?
                <ol>
                    <li><m>-\frac{1}{x}+C.</m></li>
                    <li><m>-\frac{1}{a}+C.</m></li>
                    <li><m>-\frac{1}{a}.</m></li>
                    <li><m>-\frac{1}{a}+1.</m></li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Fevaluatexcube">
            <p>
                Using your choice in <xref ref="activity-T8Fabound"/>, what is <me>\lim_{a\to \infty} \int_1^a \frac{1}{x^2} dx?</me>
            </p>
        </activity>
        
        <activity xml:id="activity-T8Fcos">
            <task>
                <p>
                    Find <m>\int_{\pi/2}^a \cos(x)dx.</m>
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    Which of the following is true about <m>\int_{\pi/2}^\infty \cos(x)dx</m>?
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\int_{\pi/2}^\infty \cos(x)dx</m> is a real number.</li>
                        <li><m>\int_{\pi/2}^\infty \cos(x)dx</m> is positive infinity.</li>
                        <li><m>\int_{\pi/2}^\infty \cos(x)dx</m> is negative infinity.</li>
                        <li><m>\int_{\pi/2}^\infty \cos(x)dx</m> is undefined.</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </task>
            
        </activity>
        
        <definition xml:id="definition-TI8assympint">
            <p>
                For a function <m>f(x)</m> with a vertical assymptote at <m>x=b</m> and a constant <m>c</m>, we let <m>\displaystyle \int_c^b f(x) dx</m> denote <me>\int_c^b f(x) dx=\lim_{b\to a}\left( \int_c^a f(x) dx\right).</me>  
            </p>
            <p>
                Similarly <me>\int_{b}^c f(x) dx=\lim_{a\to b}\left( \int_a^c f(x) dx\right).</me>
            </p>
        </definition>
        
        
