        <activity xml:id="activity-TI8prule1">
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Suppose that <m>0&lt; p</m> and <m>p\neq 1</m>.  Consider <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{1}{x^p}\ dx=\frac{1}{(1-p)}x^{1-p}+C</m>.
                </p>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <p>
                    If <m>p&lt; 1</m>, what is <m>\displaystyle \int_1^\infty \frac{1}{x^p}\ dx</m>?
                </p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    If <m>p> 1</m>, what is <m>\displaystyle \int_1^\infty \frac{1}{x^p}\ dx</m>?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        
        
